The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Patil to be at helm of UTI asset firm

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Patil: Top slot

 Mumbai, Jan. 13: R. H. Patil has been appointed as the chairman of UTI Asset Management Co, the country?s leading mutual fund. A press statement said Patil has been appointed with the concurrence of UTI Trustee Co Pvt Ltd. 

 Patil has been closely associated with the financial sector and the capital market in particular, in various capacities. 

 His most notable stint has been as the chairman of the National Stock Exchange. Instrumental in setting up the National Stock Exchange of India Ltd (NSEIL), he was its first managing director and chief executive officer.

 NSEIL has radically transformed and upgraded the Indian capital markets as one of the best in the world in terms of efficiency in trading and settlement. In terms of number of transactions per day, NSEIL is third largest in the world after New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq. 

 Patil?s association with the financial sector started in 1968 when he joined the erstwhile economic department of the Reserve Bank of India after a two-year stint on the faculty of the post graduate department of economics in the University of Bombay.

 He joined Industrial Development Bank of India in 1975 and was its executive director in charge of direct loans, treasury functions, research and planning and merchant banking activities.

 He was appointed as the managing director and CEO of National Stock Exchange in 1993. 

 After retiring from the National Stock Exchange, he became chairman of The Clearing Corporation of India Ltd in May 2001. He has also served as the chairman of the Disinvestment Commission from July 2001 to May 2004.




